From a94bb9faab2c4d40087a7af5d11cf8d291989e4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 6 Jun 2025 10:03:40 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 08/10] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Apply best power mode for 6
 GHz channels

Currently, during the AP interface bringup, the user has to specify
the power mode for the 6 GHz interface. if the power mode is not
specified, then LPI is applied by default.
If no power mode is specified during channel change, then the current
power mode is applied.

This has the following issues:
    1. The default power mode is LPI, which may not be the best power
       mode for all the channels.
    2. Additional overhead for the user to know all the power values
       for all the channels for every power mode, if the user wants
       to set best power mode for the channel.
    3. If the current power mode is invalid for a new channel, then
       the channel change fails.

To fix this, add logic in hostapd to apply the best power mode for
the 6 GHz channels during Vap bringup and channel change.

Also, add additional logic to apply the best power mode during AFC
power info processing.

Export the static API 'hostapd_switch_power_mode' for use in
other files.

Add best power mode as a fallback in the following cases:
    1. If the user configured power mode during channel change is
       invalid for the target channel, apply the best power mode
       instead.
    2. If the user configured power mode is invalid for the current
       channel, apply the best power mode instead.
    3. If random channel selection fails to find a valid channel,
       apply the best power mode for the target channel.

Introduce a new iface config 'enable_best_power_mode' to enable
calculation of best power mode support for 6 GHz channels.

